natural problem: Karen drove continuously from 9:40 a.m. until 1:20 p.m. of the same day and covered a distance of 165 miles. What was her average speed in miles per hour?
natural solution: Average speed is defined as distance traveled divided by time traveled. Karen drove 165 miles in $3\frac{40}{60}=3\frac{2}{3}=\frac{11}{3}$ hours, so her average speed was $\frac{165}{\frac{11}{3}}=3\cdot15=\boxed{45}$ miles per hour.

fixes distance :: real
and start_time end_time :: "nat \<Rightarrow> nat"
and average_speed :: real
assumes h0 : "distance = 165"
and h1 : "start_time = 9*60 + 40"
and h2 : "end_time = 13*60 + 20"
and h3 : "average_speed = distance / ((end_time - start_time) / 60)"
shows  "average_speed = 45"
